# JavaScript Function Basics

```javascript
// Function declaration
function sum(a, b) {
    return a + b;
}

// Function expression
const multiply = function(x, y) {
    return x * y;
};

console.log(sum(5, 10)); // 15
console.log(multiply(3, 4)); // 12
```

### Function Characteristics

| Property | Description |
|----------|-------------|
| Reusable | Functions can be called multiple times. |
| Modular | Encourages code decomposition into smaller units. |
| Encapsulation | Isolates code functionality. |

# Promises for Async Operations

```javascript
// Creating a promise
const fetchData = () => {
    return new Promise((resolve, reject) => {
        // Simulate an API call
        setTimeout(() => {
            const data = { message: 'Hello World' };
            resolve(data);
        }, 1000);
    });
};

// Consuming the promise
fetchData().then(data => console.log(data));
```

### Promise States

| State | Description |
|-------|-------------|
| Pending | Initial state, neither fulfilled nor rejected. |
| Fulfilled | Operation completed successfully. |
| Rejected | Operation failed. |

# Understanding 'this' in JavaScript

```javascript
// Global Context
console.log(this); // In browser, refers to window

// Function Context
function showThis() {
    console.log(this);
}

// Method Context
const obj = {
    name: 'JavaScript',
    display: function() {
        console.log(this.name);
    }
};

showThis(); // In non-strict mode, refers to global object
obj.display(); // Refers to obj
```

### Context Usage

| Context | 'this' Reference |
|---------|------------------|
| Global | Global Object |
| Function | Caller Object or Global Object |
| Method | Object Owning Method |

# JavaScript Closures Explained

```javascript
function makeCounter() {
    let count = 0;
    return function() {
        return count++;
    };
}

const counter = makeCounter();
console.log(counter()); // 0
console.log(counter()); // 1
```

### Benefits of Closures

| Feature | Description |
|---------|-------------|
| Private Data | Enables data hiding and encapsulation. |
| Stateful Functions | Remembers state across function calls. |
| Module Pattern | Aids in organizing code into units. |
